@Reasoning
apply_devirt_candidate_exact applies a single exact devirtualization
transform identified by index into wpa.devirtualization_candidates.

Bucket 0x0002 dispatches here when the candidate's confidence/is_speculative
flag indicates exact devirtualization (a unique implementation was proven).
Replaces a CALL_INDIRECT (opcode 20305) with a direct CALL (opcode 20304)
to the proven target function.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Reads candidate from wpa.devirtualization_candidates (offset 104 of WPA)
at the given index. Per E1 normalization, the candidate is the canonical
40-byte form: call_site(0), target_function(8), confidence(16),
verified(24), is_speculative(32).

For exact devirt (is_speculative == 0 / confidence == 1): rewrite the call
site instruction's opcode from CALL_INDIRECT to CALL and overwrite operand
0 with target_function. Mirrors lines 2437-2447 of apply_devirtualization.

Returns 1 on successful rewrite, 0 on no-op (index out of range, null
candidate, wrong opcode, or speculative flag set).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1). One List index lookup, three memory_set_int64 writes. Sub-microsecond.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Compile-time only. Soundness depends on identify_virtual_call_elimination
having correctly verified the candidate (the `verified` field). This
wrapper trusts the WPA filter; over-aggressive devirt is a type-confusion
risk at runtime, but the trust boundary is at WPA, not here.
@End Security_Scope

