@Implementation
Reads wpa.specialization_candidates at WPA offset 160 (added by Layer 1).
At the given index, retrieves the candidate. Calls the existing
create_specialized_functions machinery wrapped for a single candidate.

For the bootstrap-phase implementation, we build a single-entry Dictionary
from (callee_id -> const_args_pattern) and pass it to
create_specialized_functions; the returned count tells us whether
specialization actually happened.

Returns 1 on successful specialization, 0 on no-op.
